      <body>
         <entry xml:id="privataot-ys"
            type="mainEntry"
            xml:lang="en"
            prev="#"
            next="#"
            source="Yalkut Shimoni">
            <form type="lemma">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">פריבטאות</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">prybṭʾwt</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic">privaṭaʾot</pron>
               <gramGrp>
                  <gram type="pos">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen">m.</gram>
                  <gram type="num">pl.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="privataot-ys-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>public baths</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <quote>τὰ πριουᾶτα</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="la">
                  <quote>privata</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>א"ר לוי לית הכא מילכו, אלא למלך שהיה מטייל על פתח פלטין וראה בולרין אחת [מושלכת]. אמ' מה נעשה לה, מהן אומ' דימוסיאות, מהן אומ' 
                     <app>
                        <lem>פרדכסיות</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#W">פריבטאות</rdg>
                     </app>. אמ' המלך אנדרטין אני עושה אותה מי מעכב.</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq 13</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 37: 55</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">אנדרטין</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">בולרין</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">דימוסיאות</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>R. Levi said: There is no taking counsel here, but it may be compared to a king who was walking at the door of his palace when he saw a chunk lying about. Said he: “What shall we do with it?” Some answered: “[Use it in building] public baths”; others answered: “private baths”. “I will make a statue of it”, declared the kind. Who then can hinder him? (Cf. Freedman / Simon I 60)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 8,8 [I 62: 2]</bibl></note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>Cf. <bibl type="modern">Krauss, LW II 488b</bibl>. Cf. <bibl type="ancient">GenR</bibl> <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="privatiyyot.html">פרבטיות</ref>. The reading <term xml:lang="jpa">פרדכסיות</term> <term xml:lang="fjb">prdksywt</term> of Ms Ox (and S) is apparently a corruption.</note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl>
                  <title>Sokoloff, DJPA</title>
                  <citedRange>506b</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
